{{M1 year in topic}}
[[File:Eadwig - MS Royal 14 B VI.jpg|{{Largethumb}}|right|[[Eadwig]], king of [[Kingdom of England|England]] (r. 955–959)]]
Year '''957''' ('''[[Roman numerals|CMLVII]]''') was a [[common year starting on Thursday]] (link will display the full calendar) of the [[Julian calendar]].

== Events ==
&lt;onlyinclude&gt;

=== By place ===

==== Europe ====
* [[September 6]] &amp;ndash; [[Liudolf, Duke of Swabia|Liudolf]], the eldest son of King [[Otto I, Holy Roman Emperor|Otto I]], dies of a violent [[fever]] near [[Pombia]] (it is rumored from a latent poison administered somehow by Berengar II's agents). The German armies return home, leaving [[Berengar II of Italy|Berengar of Ivrea]] in control of [[Kingdom of Italy (Holy Roman Empire)|Italy]]. Liudolf is succeeded by his 3-year-old son [[Otto I, Duke of Swabia and Bavaria|Otto]], who will be adopted and raised by his grandfather Otto, as the later duke of [[Duchy of Swabia|Swabia]] and [[Duchy of Bavaria|Bavaria]].
* [[Wilfred II of Besalú|Wilfred II]], count of [[County of Besalú|Besalú]] of the [[House of Barcelona]], is killed by rebellious [[vassal]]s. He is succeeded by his brother [[Sunifred II of Cerdanya|Sunifred II]].

==== England ====
* [[Mercia]] and [[Kingdom of Northumbria|Northumbria]] rebel against King [[Eadwig]] and switch their allegiance to his brother [[Edgar the Peaceful|Edgar]]. The English nobles (in support of the church) agree to divide the kingdom along the [[River Thames|Thames River]], with Eadwig keeping [[Wessex]] and [[Kent]] in the south and Edgar ruling in the north.&lt;ref&gt;Herbermann, Charles, ed. (1913). &quot;St. Dunstan&quot; ''[[Catholic Encyclopedia]]''. New York: Robert Appleton Company.&lt;/ref&gt; Edgar's advisers recall [[Dunstan]] from [[County of Flanders|Flanders]] (see [[956]]).

==== Japan ====
* The [[Tenryaku]] era under the reign of Emperor [[Emperor Murakami|Murakami]] ends. The [[Tentoku]] era begins (until [[961]]).

==== Caspian Sea ====
*[[957 Caspian Sea earthquake]]. It took place in the [[Caspian Sea]] and its vicinity. The earthquake is mentioned by several [[Arabs|Arab]] and [[Assyrian people|Syriac]] [[chronicle]] writers, who claimed that it mainly affected the region of [[Persian Iraq]]. The initial shocks lasted 40 days, but ceased for a while . The main earthquake then occurred, damaging the cities of [[Ray, Iran|Ray]], [[Talikan]], and [[Hulwan]]. A reported number of 150 villages were supposedly destroyed by the earthquake. &lt;ref name=&quot;Antonopoulos&quot;&gt;Antonopoulos, 1980&lt;/ref&gt;

=== By topic ===

==== Religion ====
* [[Olga of Kiev]], ruler and [[regent]] of [[Kievan Rus']], converts to the [[Eastern Orthodox Church]], from [[paganism]] (approximate date).
* In [[China]] the [[Longquan Monastery]] is founded during the [[Liao dynasty|Liao Dynasty]].
&lt;/onlyinclude&gt;
== Births ==
* [[Fujiwara no Junshi]], Japanese empress consort (d. [[1017]])
* [[Fujiwara no Kinsue]], Japanese statesman (d. [[1029]])
* [[Fujiwara no Sanesuke]], Japanese [[Nobility|nobleman]] (d. [[1046]])
* [[Fujiwara no Yoshikane]], Japanese nobleman (d. [[1021]])
* [[Lu Zhen]], Chinese [[scholar-official]] (approximate date)
* [[Wang Dan (Song dynasty)|Wang Dan]], Chinese politician and [[Grand Chancellor of China|Grand Chancellor]] (d. 1017)

== Deaths ==
